WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.500 --> 00:00:09.375
["Where Did You Sleep Last Night"
by Charlie Harper plays]

2
00:00:20.041 --> 00:00:22.041
[music stops]

3
00:00:23.708 --> 00:00:24.708
[groans]

4
00:00:25.083 --> 00:00:30.500
<i>â™ª My girl. my girl
Don't lie to me â™ª</i>

5
00:00:30.583 --> 00:00:34.791
<i>â™ª Tell me where did you sleep last night â™ª</i>

6
00:00:35.458 --> 00:00:37.708
[Don on recording] <i>It was
all Grace's idea. okay?</i>

7
00:00:38.750 --> 00:00:40.833
<i>She masterminded the whole thing...</i>

8
00:00:40.916 --> 00:00:42.958
[Zinhle] Ndu. move. Ndu. move.

9
00:00:43.041 --> 00:00:43.958
[Ndu] No. Zinhle!

10
00:00:44.041 --> 00:00:45.250
- [Zinhle] Move!
- [gun firing]

11
00:00:47.208 --> 00:00:50.666
<i>â™ª My girl. my girl â™ª</i>

12
00:00:52.666 --> 00:00:54.250
<i>â™ª Don't lie to me â™ª</i>

13
00:00:54.333 --> 00:00:55.458
[groans]

14
00:00:58.208 --> 00:01:01.375
<i>â™ª My girl. my girl â™ª</i>

15
00:01:02.125 --> 00:01:03.250
[in Xhosa] Son?

16
00:01:03.333 --> 00:01:06.083
<i>â™ª Don't lie to me â™ª</i>

17
00:01:07.458 --> 00:01:08.791
Son?

18
00:01:13.958 --> 00:01:15.541
[in English] What have you done?

19
00:01:16.166 --> 00:01:17.208
Bitch!

20
00:01:18.166 --> 00:01:19.250
Zinhle...

21
00:01:19.791 --> 00:01:20.833
Shit!

22
00:01:20.916 --> 00:01:22.041
Come back here!

23
00:01:22.125 --> 00:01:23.805
- [gunshot]
- [in Xhosa] Zinhle! Come back!

24
00:01:23.833 --> 00:01:25.750
- [gun clicking]
- [in English] Shit!

25
00:01:26.333 --> 00:01:27.166
[tires screeching]

26
00:01:27.250 --> 00:01:29.625
Zinhle! Zinhle. come back here!

27
00:01:30.208 --> 00:01:31.833
Zinhle. come back here!

28
00:01:32.666 --> 00:01:35.416
[Grace] <i>Don is medically insane.</i>

29
00:01:35.500 --> 00:01:36.833
A decision was made.

30
00:01:38.541 --> 00:01:40.833
I'm stepping in as CEO.

31
00:01:41.625 --> 00:01:45.541
This medical report cannot be
the final say on Don's mental condition.

32
00:01:45.625 --> 00:01:47.916
Bhengu Beauty's reputation
is in the gutter.

33
00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:50.041
We cannot afford a public legal matter.

34
00:01:50.125 --> 00:01:53.041
[in Afrikaans and English]
No. no. no. no. Bra Don should be here.

35
00:01:53.125 --> 00:01:54.750
[in English] Ladies and gentlemen.

36
00:01:55.458 --> 00:01:59.083
in the case of Don's
mental incapacitation. I step in.

37
00:02:00.041 --> 00:02:01.333
<i>It's in the MOI.</i>

38
00:02:02.291 --> 00:02:03.291
[in Xhosa] Son...

39
00:02:03.958 --> 00:02:04.958
Son...

40
00:02:06.666 --> 00:02:07.708
Son...

41
00:02:08.208 --> 00:02:09.250
[in English] Oh. shit.

42
00:02:10.458 --> 00:02:11.458
Don't move.

43
00:02:13.250 --> 00:02:14.416
The shooter stole my car.

44
00:02:14.500 --> 00:02:17.500
Her name is Zinhle. The Face of Bhengu.

45
00:02:17.583 --> 00:02:19.666
[in Xhosa and English]
Find her. and keep her for me.

46
00:02:19.750 --> 00:02:22.666
[in English] Tomorrow Don marries a child.

47
00:02:23.250 --> 00:02:25.958
whom he proposed to only a few days ago.

48
00:02:26.041 --> 00:02:28.000
[sirens wailing]

49
00:02:28.583 --> 00:02:33.083
[sobs] Please live.
Please live. Please. please.

50
00:02:35.083 --> 00:02:37.375
[groans] Love your family.

51
00:02:39.416 --> 00:02:42.958
[breathes erratically]
I... We're all you have.

52
00:02:43.041 --> 00:02:45.041
[sirens wailing]

53
00:02:45.708 --> 00:02:47.083
[Don's voice breaks] Ndumiso...

54
00:02:47.583 --> 00:02:49.250
[in Zulu and Xhosa] Help has arrived.

55
00:02:49.333 --> 00:02:50.416
[sniffles]

56
00:02:50.500 --> 00:02:52.625
[Grace in English]
<i>He is a ticking time bomb.</i>

57
00:02:53.666 --> 00:02:55.916
<i>a reckless law unto himself.</i>

58
00:02:56.500 --> 00:02:58.583
<i>If this madman remains CEO.</i>

59
00:02:58.666 --> 00:03:01.541
there will be no Bhengu Beauty
to speak of in months.

60
00:03:01.625 --> 00:03:04.708
[phone buzzes]

61
00:03:04.791 --> 00:03:06.333
[suspenseful music plays]

62
00:03:06.416 --> 00:03:07.458
Excuse me.

63
00:03:07.541 --> 00:03:08.958
[expels breath] Yeah?

64
00:03:09.958 --> 00:03:13.666
The decision to install me as CEO

65
00:03:14.583 --> 00:03:15.666
must be upheld.

66
00:03:16.291 --> 00:03:19.833
All in favor of upholding
Mrs. Bhengu's new position?

67
00:03:32.708 --> 00:03:33.708
[Phila clears throat]

68
00:03:34.500 --> 00:03:37.041
[whispers] There's a situation
at the house.

69
00:03:38.291 --> 00:03:40.291
[music continues playing]

70
00:03:41.791 --> 00:03:44.125
- Why are you stopping?
- [paramedic] I'm sorry. he's gone.

71
00:03:44.208 --> 00:03:45.541
No. no! No. no!

72
00:03:46.333 --> 00:03:47.333
Wake him.

73
00:03:48.291 --> 00:03:49.333
Wake him!

74
00:03:49.916 --> 00:03:51.291
He's going to be fine. right?

75
00:03:52.625 --> 00:03:54.625
[mournful music plays]

76
00:03:55.583 --> 00:03:58.625
[imperceptible]

77
00:04:12.458 --> 00:04:13.458
[in Sotho] No.

78
00:04:14.083 --> 00:04:18.500
[Grace screams in English]
No! No. Ndumiso. no!

79
00:04:18.583 --> 00:04:22.375
[screams echoing] No. no. no. no! No!

80
00:04:25.250 --> 00:04:32.000
[Grace wailing] No!

81
00:04:33.875 --> 00:04:35.875
[continues wailing]

82
00:04:42.791 --> 00:04:43.916
[music fades]

83
00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:46.416
I had found out that Zinhle is a criminal<i>...</i>

84
00:04:47.625 --> 00:04:49.291
[in Xhosa]...working with her brother

85
00:04:49.375 --> 00:04:50.875
[in English] to sabotage my family.

86
00:04:52.416 --> 00:04:55.125
[in Xhosa] I broke out of the trunk
and took my gun...

87
00:04:55.208 --> 00:04:56.625
[in English]...from the cubbyhole.

88
00:04:57.833 --> 00:05:01.166
[in Xhosa] When I approached the door.
I heard voices.

89
00:05:03.375 --> 00:05:04.958
[in English] I thought...

90
00:05:06.541 --> 00:05:08.916
[in Xhosa]...she was
with an accomplice but...

91
00:05:10.166 --> 00:05:11.166
it was Ndumiso.

92
00:05:13.666 --> 00:05:16.106
[in English. starts crying]
I don't even know why he returned.

93
00:05:16.875 --> 00:05:19.125
[in Sotho] Because you wanted to marry
his girlfriend!

94
00:05:22.750 --> 00:05:24.583
[English] I don't know
what she said to him.

95
00:05:24.666 --> 00:05:26.000
but he wanted to talk.

96
00:05:27.083 --> 00:05:30.291
[in Xhosa] He begged us to drop our guns.

97
00:05:31.083 --> 00:05:32.323
[in English] I complied. and...

98
00:05:33.125 --> 00:05:35.083
Zinhle saw an opportunity.

99
00:05:35.166 --> 00:05:38.708
missed. and shot... [sniffles]

100
00:05:38.791 --> 00:05:40.375
[voice breaks] Shot Ndumiso.

101
00:05:40.458 --> 00:05:43.250
- And even after that. she kept shooting.
- [sobs]

102
00:05:43.333 --> 00:05:46.958
- Ndumiso tried to stop...
- You could have stopped her. Don!

103
00:05:47.625 --> 00:05:49.625
You did this! You let her kill our son!

104
00:05:49.708 --> 00:05:51.250
No. it's not his fault.

105
00:05:51.333 --> 00:05:52.875
No. Phila. no!

106
00:05:53.625 --> 00:05:57.958
I told you. Don.
I told you not to trust that girl.

107
00:05:58.041 --> 00:06:00.041
Instead. you throw me and Phila out...

108
00:06:00.125 --> 00:06:03.000
[in Sotho]...because wanted more children.
Now our son is dead.

109
00:06:03.083 --> 00:06:05.083
[in English]
That's... That's enough. Mom. please.

110
00:06:06.125 --> 00:06:08.875
It's enough. It's enough now.

111
00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:18.000
[officer] I have a few more questions
for you. sir.

112
00:06:19.458 --> 00:06:21.291
[Don] I have already given you all I can.

113
00:06:24.750 --> 00:06:26.030
[Phila in Sotho] Excuse me. sir.

114
00:06:26.083 --> 00:06:28.083
[in English]
This is not a good time for us.

115
00:06:28.625 --> 00:06:29.875
[in Sotho] We're doing our job.

116
00:06:29.958 --> 00:06:30.875
I understand...

117
00:06:30.958 --> 00:06:34.208
[in English]...but honestly. we just need
a little bit of time. please.

118
00:06:34.291 --> 00:06:36.541
We'd really appreciate it
if you come back tomorrow.

119
00:06:37.333 --> 00:06:39.375
[officer in Sotho]
All right. team. let's wrap up.

120
00:06:39.458 --> 00:06:40.875
We will come back tomorrow.

121
00:06:44.416 --> 00:06:47.125
[in English] Zinhle is one of the kids
from the bleaching tests.

122
00:06:48.041 --> 00:06:51.791
Bhengu Beauty launch.
the bleaching scandals.

123
00:06:51.875 --> 00:06:53.458
Kolobe's betrayal...

124
00:06:54.125 --> 00:06:55.250
She wants revenge.

125
00:06:55.833 --> 00:06:57.500
[Grace in Sotho] <i>What about the fire?</i>

126
00:06:57.583 --> 00:06:58.916
[Don in English] <i>She survived.</i>

127
00:06:59.708 --> 00:07:01.708
<i>There's something
I didn't tell the police.</i>

128
00:07:02.625 --> 00:07:05.125
<i>Zinhle made me confess to everything.</i>

129
00:07:05.208 --> 00:07:08.416
<i>The bleaching tests and the fire.</i>

130
00:07:08.916 --> 00:07:10.875
She drugged me. and that video...

131
00:07:11.583 --> 00:07:13.833
[in Xhosa]
...it's on her Bhengu Beauty laptop.

132
00:07:16.458 --> 00:07:18.166
[in English] What was that about a laptop?

133
00:07:19.791 --> 00:07:23.833
Oh. uh. Zinhle stole the laptop too.

134
00:07:25.541 --> 00:07:26.708
I need some air.

135
00:07:28.375 --> 00:07:31.416
["Where Did You Sleep Last Night"
by Charlie Harper plays]

136
00:07:48.750 --> 00:07:49.833
[glass shatters]

137
00:08:00.875 --> 00:08:03.916
<i>â™ª My girl. my girl â™ª</i>

138
00:08:04.000 --> 00:08:06.250
[exploding]

139
00:08:06.333 --> 00:08:11.291
<i>â™ª Don't lie to me â™ª</i>

140
00:08:14.958 --> 00:08:15.958
[song fades]

141
00:08:30.000 --> 00:08:32.625
[Noni in Sotho] I can't imagine
what you're going through.

142
00:08:43.291 --> 00:08:44.375
{\an8}Um...

143
00:08:45.958 --> 00:08:48.750
{\an8}[in English] I'll get started
on the funeral arrangements.

144
00:08:51.333 --> 00:08:52.791
{\an8}What would you like as the...

145
00:08:52.875 --> 00:08:57.750
{\an8}Go tell Modali Mutale to hold back
the CEO announcement.

146
00:08:59.333 --> 00:09:02.375
{\an8}[in Sotho] Make sure
no one tells your father...

147
00:09:02.458 --> 00:09:03.738
{\an8}[in English]...until it's time.

148
00:09:09.125 --> 00:09:10.125
{\an8}Ma.

149
00:09:10.541 --> 00:09:12.500
{\an8}Ndu just died. and you're worried...

150
00:09:12.583 --> 00:09:16.708
{\an8}[angrily] Don't you ever...
ever think you know how I feel.

151
00:09:21.291 --> 00:09:23.708
{\an8}It's your father's fault
that Ndumiso is gone.

152
00:09:23.791 --> 00:09:25.951
{\an8}[in Sotho] Do you want him
to have everything else too?

153
00:09:26.791 --> 00:09:28.791
{\an8}[tense music plays]

154
00:09:31.125 --> 00:09:32.750
{\an8}[in English] Mutale first.

155
00:09:34.791 --> 00:09:35.791
{\an8}then...

156
00:09:36.916 --> 00:09:38.458
{\an8}the funeral arrangements.

157
00:09:45.833 --> 00:09:47.541
{\an8}[music fades]

158
00:09:48.916 --> 00:09:51.166
{\an8}[Phila sighs deeply]

159
00:09:54.625 --> 00:09:56.083
Put me back together. Noni.

160
00:09:56.166 --> 00:09:57.500
[intriguing harp music plays]

161
00:09:59.125 --> 00:10:01.333
Are you close to finding
Zinhle and the video?

162
00:10:01.916 --> 00:10:03.958
[Simphiwe in Sotho]
She wasn't at the Soweto house.

163
00:10:04.041 --> 00:10:07.208
Bonga's boss might offer a clue.

164
00:10:07.791 --> 00:10:09.875
[in English] What about the police
from last night?

165
00:10:09.958 --> 00:10:11.291
No. they're off the case.

166
00:10:11.791 --> 00:10:14.625
My boys and I are now in charge. hey?
[chuckles]

167
00:10:18.458 --> 00:10:19.541
Why are you still here?

168
00:10:20.125 --> 00:10:21.208
Huh?

169
00:10:21.291 --> 00:10:22.291
[Don] Go.

170
00:10:22.958 --> 00:10:24.958
Go find Zinhle and the video.

171
00:10:28.541 --> 00:10:29.541
[Don clicks tongue]

172
00:10:30.041 --> 00:10:32.041
[harp music continues playing]

173
00:10:38.541 --> 00:10:39.541
Chancer...

174
00:10:40.541 --> 00:10:43.416
- [in Sotho] I need your help.
- Oh?

175
00:10:44.166 --> 00:10:46.833
Like you did when you wanted to win
The Face of Bhengu?

176
00:10:46.916 --> 00:10:48.083
Mm?

177
00:10:48.166 --> 00:10:50.041
[in English and Sotho]
Or when you told Bonga

178
00:10:50.125 --> 00:10:51.416
to get a gun from me?

179
00:10:53.125 --> 00:10:55.250
[in English] You know what.
if it wasn't for you.

180
00:10:55.750 --> 00:10:56.910
he'd probably still be alive.

181
00:10:56.958 --> 00:10:58.500
That was my brother.

182
00:10:59.541 --> 00:11:00.916
His death won't be in vain.

183
00:11:02.083 --> 00:11:04.583
[in Sotho] I'm one step away
from finishing this.

184
00:11:19.375 --> 00:11:22.125
[in English] For a life
to be taken so tragically.

185
00:11:22.791 --> 00:11:24.083
and so young.

186
00:11:24.166 --> 00:11:27.333
[Phila clears throat] Uh. Mam' Mutale.

187
00:11:28.416 --> 00:11:32.000
my father can't know
about the change in leadership

188
00:11:32.083 --> 00:11:34.166
until after the announcement
has been made...

189
00:11:34.250 --> 00:11:36.583
There's an embargo on the announcement.

190
00:11:37.291 --> 00:11:40.458
And why is this even on your mind?
You just lost your only brother.

191
00:11:40.541 --> 00:11:43.291
You should take a break
from running your mother's errands.

192
00:11:43.375 --> 00:11:47.291
The board members. um.
need to be kept tight-lipped.

193
00:11:47.375 --> 00:11:48.625
especially Lovers.

194
00:11:51.708 --> 00:11:53.708
[intriguing piano music plays]

195
00:11:56.541 --> 00:11:57.750
[music stops]

196
00:11:57.833 --> 00:11:59.500
- [radio on laptop starts playing]
- Oh.

197
00:12:03.375 --> 00:12:04.291
I mean...

198
00:12:04.375 --> 00:12:06.416
[in Sotho]...I can fix the screen.

199
00:12:06.500 --> 00:12:09.375
but I have to open it
to check if the hard drive is still fine.

200
00:12:09.875 --> 00:12:11.583
Chancer. I need that video.

201
00:12:12.208 --> 00:12:13.125
[in English] Then what?

202
00:12:13.208 --> 00:12:16.166
And then the world will know
who the Bhengus really are.

203
00:12:16.250 --> 00:12:21.208
[in Sotho] I'm begging you.
do whatever you have to do to fix it.

204
00:12:21.291 --> 00:12:22.583
[announcer] <i>Welcome to news...</i>

205
00:12:22.666 --> 00:12:24.267
- I'll pay you for it.
- [in English] Okay.

206
00:12:24.291 --> 00:12:26.642
[announcer in English]
<i>...the son of beauty mogul. Don Bhengu.</i>

207
00:12:26.666 --> 00:12:29.666
<i>was shot and killed
at the Bhengu home late last night.</i>

208
00:12:29.750 --> 00:12:33.500
<i>The suspect. who is currently
The Face of Bhengu Beauty. Zinhle Manzini.</i>

209
00:12:33.583 --> 00:12:34.750
<i>is on the run.</i>

210
00:12:34.833 --> 00:12:37.193
<i>- More details on this breaking story...</i>
- [turns off radio]

211
00:12:38.375 --> 00:12:40.375
[gentle harp music plays]

212
00:12:40.958 --> 00:12:43.291
[shaky breathing] Um...

213
00:12:44.916 --> 00:12:48.208
I need to freshen up
and borrow some clothes.

214
00:12:48.291 --> 00:12:49.416
On... On your left.

215
00:12:50.500 --> 00:12:52.041
I have to get out of here.

216
00:12:56.500 --> 00:13:00.208
[sobbing]

217
00:13:11.458 --> 00:13:13.458
[phone buzzes]

218
00:13:13.541 --> 00:13:14.375
[music fades]

219
00:13:14.458 --> 00:13:15.583
What?

220
00:13:15.666 --> 00:13:17.125
[Lovers] <i>We need to talk. bra Don.</i>

221
00:13:17.208 --> 00:13:19.458
Lovers. I'm not in the mood to talk.

222
00:13:20.000 --> 00:13:22.166
<i>Mutale is calling but...</i>

223
00:13:22.250 --> 00:13:24.250
[Grace] Has Ndumiso's killer been found?

224
00:13:24.916 --> 00:13:26.116
[in Xhosa] I'll call you back.

225
00:13:28.166 --> 00:13:30.226
- [in English] I have it handled.
- [Grace] When. Don?

226
00:13:30.250 --> 00:13:31.458
I told you I'm handling it!

227
00:13:34.666 --> 00:13:36.666
[tense music plays]

228
00:13:40.541 --> 00:13:41.666
[Phila clears throat]

229
00:13:45.625 --> 00:13:49.666
Um. Linda and Thando
wanted to be here for...

230
00:13:50.416 --> 00:13:51.416
[Linda] Look. I...

231
00:13:52.916 --> 00:13:56.083
I obviously knew that Zinhle
was up to something.

232
00:13:57.083 --> 00:13:59.791
- I just wish I had fought harder.
- [phone pings]

233
00:14:00.291 --> 00:14:03.250
[Phila clears throat] Sorry.
the funeral planner is on his way

234
00:14:03.333 --> 00:14:05.458
just to help with the arrangements.

235
00:14:06.625 --> 00:14:07.708
[Regina clears throat]

236
00:14:08.500 --> 00:14:09.416
Madam...

237
00:14:09.500 --> 00:14:12.380
[in Xhosa]...you still haven't told us
what to prepare for the visitors.

238
00:14:12.916 --> 00:14:14.625
[in Sotho] Figure it out. Regina.

239
00:14:14.708 --> 00:14:16.668
- [in Zulu] I'll help you.
- [in Xhosa] Thank you.

240
00:14:16.708 --> 00:14:18.625
[in English] I know
how you prefer things done.

241
00:14:19.875 --> 00:14:21.000
We all loved him.

242
00:14:25.041 --> 00:14:28.208
I'll help with the funeral arrangements
with Phila.

243
00:14:29.625 --> 00:14:30.666
Linda...

244
00:14:38.291 --> 00:14:40.291
[heartfelt music plays]

245
00:14:43.333 --> 00:14:45.333
[Don] I know we've had our differences.

246
00:14:48.750 --> 00:14:50.416
I'm glad you're here.

247
00:14:55.750 --> 00:14:56.875
[Phila] <i>These are wrong.</i>

248
00:14:57.500 --> 00:15:00.458
Wrong. Where are all the pictures
of him smiling?

249
00:15:01.041 --> 00:15:04.708
Oh. um. I saw those. but they were giving
a bit of a festive feel.

250
00:15:04.791 --> 00:15:05.791
Festive?

251
00:15:06.583 --> 00:15:08.541
[Linda] Just use the ones that we prefer.

252
00:15:09.125 --> 00:15:09.958
Thank you.

253
00:15:10.041 --> 00:15:12.583
- Let's look at the next thing.
- Okay. um...

254
00:15:12.666 --> 00:15:15.541
[nervously] These are flower options.

255
00:15:15.625 --> 00:15:17.291
These look good. Phila. come.

256
00:15:19.625 --> 00:15:20.875
Okay. C. We're winning.

257
00:15:21.541 --> 00:15:23.750
My brother loved lilies.
These are perfect.

258
00:15:24.291 --> 00:15:27.833
Uh. unfortunately.
we are currently out of lilies.

259
00:15:27.916 --> 00:15:29.666
What the fuck are we paying you for?

260
00:15:30.375 --> 00:15:31.958
Oh. you see. sir.

261
00:15:32.041 --> 00:15:35.166
our... our suppliers
currently can't really...

262
00:15:35.250 --> 00:15:38.916
Do me a favor. Just take a walk with me.

263
00:15:39.000 --> 00:15:40.000
Okay.

264
00:15:41.166 --> 00:15:45.208
I want you to say "can't" one more time.

265
00:15:45.291 --> 00:15:46.531
- [Linda] Phila...
- No. no. no.

266
00:15:46.916 --> 00:15:50.250
Say "can't."
I dare you to say "can't" one more time!

267
00:15:50.333 --> 00:15:56.000
This is... Ndumiso's
one and only funeral. Linda. Okay?

268
00:15:56.083 --> 00:15:57.083
He's not coming back.

269
00:15:57.125 --> 00:16:00.916
We don't get another shot at this.
This is not a fucking rehearsal. okay?

270
00:16:01.000 --> 00:16:02.916
So if I say that we want lilies.

271
00:16:03.000 --> 00:16:05.666
then you get on a plane
and get them from another country

272
00:16:05.750 --> 00:16:06.958
if you have to!

273
00:16:07.791 --> 00:16:09.791
Fuck. man! They're just flowers!

274
00:16:11.041 --> 00:16:12.041
Please leave.

275
00:16:15.041 --> 00:16:16.125
[music fades]

276
00:16:17.625 --> 00:16:19.958
[Makhosi Mnisi in Zulu] I warned you.
[sniffles]

277
00:16:20.583 --> 00:16:25.833
When you called me crying in the street
with your brother's dead body...

278
00:16:25.916 --> 00:16:26.750
[sniffles]

279
00:16:26.833 --> 00:16:30.041
...I told you not to go back.

280
00:16:30.833 --> 00:16:32.513
[in Sotho] I needed a confession from Don.

281
00:16:32.541 --> 00:16:36.208
[in Zulu] That's because
there's always one more thing with you.

282
00:16:39.125 --> 00:16:41.833
[in Sotho] Makhosi.
I have nowhere else to go.

283
00:16:41.916 --> 00:16:43.125
[scoffs]

284
00:16:43.708 --> 00:16:46.291
[in Zulu]
I can't help you anymore. my girl.

285
00:16:47.375 --> 00:16:51.583
I'm no longer compromising
my spiritual gifts for you.

286
00:16:51.666 --> 00:16:53.666
I can't help you anymore.

287
00:16:53.750 --> 00:16:56.791
[news anchor] <i>A reward of R500.000
has been offered</i>

288
00:16:56.875 --> 00:16:59.583
<i>for anyone with credible information</i>

289
00:16:59.666 --> 00:17:05.791
<i>leading to the arrest of Miss Manzini.</i>

290
00:17:05.875 --> 00:17:06.995
[mournful organ music plays]

291
00:17:07.041 --> 00:17:08.291
Makhosi...

292
00:17:08.375 --> 00:17:12.166
<i>Miss Manzini. who is the current
face of Bhengu Beauty.</i>

293
00:17:12.250 --> 00:17:15.791
<i>is being charged
with the murder of Ndumiso Bhengu.</i>

294
00:17:15.875 --> 00:17:17.875
<i>More on this...</i>

295
00:17:17.958 --> 00:17:19.041
[in Sotho] Please take it.

296
00:17:19.791 --> 00:17:22.250
I want to thank you
for taking care of Bonga's funeral.

297
00:17:33.083 --> 00:17:34.083
Makhosi.

298
00:17:49.541 --> 00:17:50.541
[music fades]

299
00:17:52.125 --> 00:17:53.041
[Makhosi clicks tongue]

300
00:17:53.125 --> 00:17:54.833
[in Xhosa] When are you coming to bed?

301
00:17:54.916 --> 00:17:56.416
[in English] No. soon. soon.

302
00:17:56.500 --> 00:17:59.958
[breathes in deeply] It's actually strange
being back here. hey?

303
00:18:00.041 --> 00:18:01.041
After. you know...

304
00:18:02.125 --> 00:18:04.875
Yeah. But we'll be home soon.

305
00:18:04.958 --> 00:18:06.000
- Okay?
- Mm-hm.

306
00:18:06.500 --> 00:18:08.500
- Let's just do this for Ndu.
- Yeah.

307
00:18:09.125 --> 00:18:12.250
Come to bed when you're ready.

308
00:18:16.083 --> 00:18:17.750
[tense music plays]

309
00:18:43.625 --> 00:18:44.750
[Don] Does Linda know?

310
00:18:47.083 --> 00:18:48.125
[music fades]

311
00:18:49.833 --> 00:18:50.833
Huh?

312
00:18:52.125 --> 00:18:54.642
[in Xhosa and English] Does Linda know
we were sleeping together

313
00:18:54.666 --> 00:18:55.666
until the very end?

314
00:18:55.708 --> 00:18:56.708
[music resumes]

315
00:18:57.375 --> 00:18:58.916
[in English] And that you enjoyed it?

316
00:19:00.000 --> 00:19:02.000
I didn't enjoy it.

317
00:19:02.625 --> 00:19:04.708
You were supposed to give me a child.

318
00:19:08.500 --> 00:19:10.500
[tense music sting]

319
00:19:28.083 --> 00:19:29.291
[music fades]

320
00:19:29.375 --> 00:19:31.916
["Bonani! Bonani!"
[by Mandisi Dyatyis plays]

321
00:19:34.666 --> 00:19:36.708
[Phila] Thank you all for...

322
00:19:37.541 --> 00:19:40.458
for being with us
as we lay my brother to rest.

323
00:19:42.166 --> 00:19:44.250
Ndumiso and I shared a bedroom

324
00:19:44.333 --> 00:19:46.291
until he was 11 years old.

325
00:19:48.583 --> 00:19:49.625
[sniffles]

326
00:19:49.708 --> 00:19:52.708
And he always said that it was
because he didn't want me to be alone.

327
00:19:52.791 --> 00:19:53.833
[chuckles]

328
00:19:56.833 --> 00:19:59.791
But we both knew it was
because he was terrified of the dark.

329
00:20:03.416 --> 00:20:07.416
And until Ndumiso was 19 years old.

330
00:20:07.916 --> 00:20:13.125
he copied my clothes.
my hair. my swag. everything.

331
00:20:14.833 --> 00:20:16.791
[voice breaks] Ndumiso was braver...

332
00:20:20.125 --> 00:20:22.416
and truer to himself...

333
00:20:22.500 --> 00:20:24.208
[song fades]

334
00:20:26.125 --> 00:20:30.541
...than anyone I will ever. ever know.

335
00:20:34.458 --> 00:20:36.166
["Scars' by David O'Dowda plays]

336
00:20:38.041 --> 00:20:41.666
To have been loved by him
meant never having to be alone.

337
00:20:47.750 --> 00:20:52.583
<i>â™ª You stopped reminding me
Our love is a ghost â™ª</i>

338
00:20:54.041 --> 00:20:58.916
<i>â™ª My only comfort
Has survived in the smoke â™ª</i>

339
00:21:00.416 --> 00:21:04.875
<i>â™ª I'll take a minute
Just to capture a note â™ª</i>

340
00:21:06.791 --> 00:21:08.500
<i>â™ª I want it back â™ª</i>

341
00:21:08.583 --> 00:21:13.791
<i>â™ª But now it's painted
On the back of all our scars â™ª</i>

342
00:21:13.875 --> 00:21:14.875
[song stops]

343
00:21:16.833 --> 00:21:19.791
[mournful music plays]

344
00:21:39.541 --> 00:21:40.666
[music fades]

345
00:21:40.750 --> 00:21:43.958
Lovers is trying to talk to your father.
Remind Mutale.

346
00:21:44.458 --> 00:21:46.666
[sighs] Yeah.
because God forbid we should forget

347
00:21:46.750 --> 00:21:49.000
what's really important here today. right?

348
00:21:50.416 --> 00:21:51.416
Yeah.

349
00:21:54.250 --> 00:21:56.583
[intriguing music plays]

350
00:21:58.291 --> 00:22:00.000
Can I steal you for a second?

351
00:22:01.333 --> 00:22:05.750
That conversation over there.
definitely not one that we want to happen.

352
00:22:06.666 --> 00:22:07.666
I've got it.

353
00:22:16.541 --> 00:22:20.541
[in Afrikaans] This Bhengu Beauty business
and your wife. Grace...

354
00:22:21.375 --> 00:22:24.750
[In English] Apologies. Bhengu.
I need to speak to Lovers for a second.

355
00:22:24.833 --> 00:22:26.791
[sighs. in Afrikaans] What now. Mutale?

356
00:22:26.875 --> 00:22:29.916
- [in English] Not now. What did I say?
- [in Afrikaans] About what?

357
00:22:30.000 --> 00:22:32.625
- [Mutale in English] What did I say?
- [in Afrikaans] About what?

358
00:22:32.708 --> 00:22:34.291
What's going on with you. man?

359
00:22:34.375 --> 00:22:36.175
[Mutale in English]
Don't be that guy. Lovers.

360
00:22:36.250 --> 00:22:37.250
[Richard] Bhengu.

361
00:22:40.583 --> 00:22:41.583
Moloto.

362
00:22:42.666 --> 00:22:43.750
What a surprise.

363
00:22:45.583 --> 00:22:47.541
[Moloto] I came to offer my condolences.

364
00:22:48.791 --> 00:22:49.791
Thank you.

365
00:22:49.875 --> 00:22:53.041
[intriguing music plays]

366
00:23:20.875 --> 00:23:22.250
- [woman] Mmm.
- [Phila] Wait...

367
00:23:22.333 --> 00:23:24.125
You're so strong.

368
00:23:24.208 --> 00:23:26.791
- Sorry?
- [Mukheli] Lorraine is right. chief.

369
00:23:28.000 --> 00:23:29.583
We've been watching you all day.

370
00:23:29.666 --> 00:23:31.000
Call me Lola.

371
00:23:32.250 --> 00:23:33.583
[chuckles uncomfortably] Right.

372
00:23:33.666 --> 00:23:35.250
Uh. Minister Mukheli.

373
00:23:35.333 --> 00:23:37.875
I hope that you enjoyed...
[chuckles uncomfortably]

374
00:23:37.958 --> 00:23:40.791
I hope you enjoyed the gifts
that we made out to your charities.

375
00:23:40.875 --> 00:23:45.125
I personally handled them
on behalf of Bhengu Beauty.

376
00:23:45.208 --> 00:23:46.583
Babe.

377
00:23:50.083 --> 00:23:51.166
Hey. babe.

378
00:23:51.250 --> 00:23:53.083
- Hey.
- Excuse me.

379
00:23:53.166 --> 00:23:54.625
[clears throat] Hey.

380
00:23:59.458 --> 00:24:01.041
The eulogy was great.

381
00:24:01.541 --> 00:24:03.708
See? You had nothing to worry about.

382
00:24:03.791 --> 00:24:04.916
Yeah. [chuckles]

383
00:24:05.875 --> 00:24:10.875
But. um... people are waiting downstairs.
so we've got to go.

384
00:24:11.833 --> 00:24:12.750
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

385
00:24:12.833 --> 00:24:15.375
Oh. right. right. Downstairs.
Right. Excuse me.

386
00:24:16.375 --> 00:24:17.875
See you around. Phila.

387
00:24:20.500 --> 00:24:21.500
Who is that?

388
00:24:22.791 --> 00:24:24.458
I don't know who she is.

389
00:24:25.291 --> 00:24:27.583
But she does look familiar.

390
00:24:28.416 --> 00:24:31.250
[in Sotho] Oh. well. she's a hot cake.

391
00:24:31.333 --> 00:24:34.666
[in Sotho] You love yourself
some hot cakes. don't you? [giggles]

392
00:24:35.208 --> 00:24:36.666
Mm.

393
00:24:36.750 --> 00:24:40.416
So that was. um... different.

394
00:24:40.500 --> 00:24:41.666
[gentle guitar music playing]

395
00:24:41.750 --> 00:24:45.250
- You looked like a damsel in distress.
- I was.

396
00:24:45.333 --> 00:24:48.083
And thank you
for swooping in and saving me. Prince...

397
00:24:48.166 --> 00:24:50.500
Charlie. You can call me Charlie.

398
00:24:52.041 --> 00:24:53.666
That's my actual name.

399
00:24:53.750 --> 00:24:55.958
I'm not calling myself
Prince Charming or something.

400
00:24:56.041 --> 00:24:57.250
- Right.
- [both chuckle]

401
00:24:57.333 --> 00:25:01.458
- Right. Of course.
- Yeah.

402
00:25:03.916 --> 00:25:05.791
- Phila. Um...
- [chuckles] Yeah.

403
00:25:05.875 --> 00:25:07.291
[chuckles] Phila.

404
00:25:10.833 --> 00:25:14.166
Your eulogy to your brother
really was great.

405
00:25:14.250 --> 00:25:15.250
Thank you.

406
00:25:15.625 --> 00:25:16.791
Hugs?

407
00:25:16.875 --> 00:25:18.833
You look like you could use one.

408
00:25:18.916 --> 00:25:21.500
A non-creepy hug.

409
00:25:24.166 --> 00:25:25.666
Yeah. I'd like that.

410
00:25:44.958 --> 00:25:46.041
I should go.

411
00:25:49.333 --> 00:25:50.333
[Phila chuckles]

412
00:25:52.375 --> 00:25:53.541
Oh. hey. um...

413
00:25:54.750 --> 00:25:55.791
Thank you.

414
00:25:56.791 --> 00:25:58.208
For the... The hug.

415
00:25:59.458 --> 00:26:00.541
Anytime.

416
00:26:07.625 --> 00:26:09.625
[music continues playing]

417
00:26:12.541 --> 00:26:14.000
My deepest condolences.

418
00:26:15.708 --> 00:26:17.041
I know how it feels.

419
00:26:19.791 --> 00:26:22.125
Have you lost a child. Mister...

420
00:26:22.208 --> 00:26:24.000
Moloto. It's Richard.

421
00:26:26.000 --> 00:26:28.541
[sighs] I've... I've lost my wife.

422
00:26:30.041 --> 00:26:32.750
My child is still alive.
but we've lost each other too.

423
00:26:34.458 --> 00:26:35.458
Of course.

424
00:26:36.041 --> 00:26:37.333
Richard Moloto.

425
00:26:39.958 --> 00:26:42.125
[in Sotho] I'm sorry about your wife.
I didn't know.

426
00:26:42.916 --> 00:26:44.291
[in English] It's been a decade.

427
00:26:45.458 --> 00:26:46.625
It doesn't go away.

428
00:26:49.083 --> 00:26:51.208
[in Sotho] I don't know
how I'm going to cope.

429
00:26:52.208 --> 00:26:55.291
[in English] Well. they say
you find strength in your work.

430
00:26:56.041 --> 00:26:57.083
[music fades]

431
00:26:57.708 --> 00:27:00.228
[in Sotho and English]
I heard you're taking over Bhengu Beauty.

432
00:27:02.916 --> 00:27:04.375
[in Sotho] That's a big statement.

433
00:27:04.458 --> 00:27:05.583
Where did you hear that?

434
00:27:06.083 --> 00:27:07.083
The rumor mill.

435
00:27:07.916 --> 00:27:10.708
My apologies if it is untrue.

436
00:27:12.375 --> 00:27:13.695
[in English] But I hope it's not.

437
00:27:16.916 --> 00:27:19.791
[in Sotho] For what it's worth.
you should.

438
00:27:21.416 --> 00:27:26.250
Everyone knows that you are the brains
behind Bhengu Beauty.

439
00:27:26.333 --> 00:27:27.833
[gentle piano music plays]

440
00:27:43.583 --> 00:27:45.291
[music intensifies]

441
00:27:45.375 --> 00:27:47.833
[sighs deeply]

442
00:27:47.916 --> 00:27:49.291
[music crescendos]

443
00:27:49.375 --> 00:27:50.833
[eerie music plays]

444
00:27:50.916 --> 00:27:54.000
[Ndu whispering] <i>Love your family.</i>

445
00:27:55.250 --> 00:27:57.375
<i>We're all you have. We're all you have.</i>

446
00:27:57.458 --> 00:27:58.458
[music fades]

447
00:27:58.500 --> 00:28:02.000
[phone buzzes]

448
00:28:09.750 --> 00:28:11.000
Hey. Lovers.

449
00:28:12.041 --> 00:28:14.250
[in Xhosa] You've been trying
to talk to me all week.

450
00:28:14.333 --> 00:28:15.517
[Lovers in Afrikaans] <i>My God...</i>

451
00:28:15.541 --> 00:28:17.750
[in English] <i>...Grace has taken over
Bhengu Beauty.</i>

452
00:28:18.583 --> 00:28:19.666
[in English] What?

453
00:28:19.750 --> 00:28:23.208
[in English and Xhosa] <i>She and the board
say you are mentally unfit.</i>

454
00:28:23.291 --> 00:28:25.458
[in English] <i>and Mutale is trying
to shut me up.</i>

455
00:28:26.291 --> 00:28:28.726
- [in Xhosa] When is the announcement?
- [in English] <i>Tomorrow.</i>

456
00:28:28.750 --> 00:28:31.458
All right. listen. first thing tomorrow.
gather the board.

457
00:28:31.541 --> 00:28:33.166
Just make sure that they don't...

458
00:28:33.250 --> 00:28:35.250
[eerie music plays]

459
00:28:36.833 --> 00:28:38.333
<i>Bra Don? Bra Don?</i>

460
00:28:39.083 --> 00:28:41.208
Make sure that they don't know
that I'm coming.

461
00:28:42.125 --> 00:28:43.375
And Grace isn't.

462
00:28:49.125 --> 00:28:50.208
[music fades]

463
00:28:50.791 --> 00:28:51.958
[whimsical music plays]

464
00:28:52.041 --> 00:28:55.500
[Phila over video]
<i>â™ª Happy birthday to you â™ª</i>

465
00:28:55.583 --> 00:28:57.041
[Ndu] <i>Wow. bro.</i>

466
00:28:57.125 --> 00:29:00.875
[Phila] <i>â™ª Happy birthday to you â™ª</i>

467
00:29:00.958 --> 00:29:02.208
[Phila laughs]

468
00:29:02.291 --> 00:29:04.083
<i>Yo. happy birthday. bro.</i>

469
00:29:04.166 --> 00:29:06.458
[Ndu over video] <i>Dude. okay. thanks.</i>
[laughs]

470
00:29:07.083 --> 00:29:09.883
[Phila over video] <i>I just figured
you needed an upgrade on your camera.</i>

471
00:29:09.916 --> 00:29:11.333
[both laugh]

472
00:29:11.416 --> 00:29:13.500
<i>Wow. thanks a lot. man.
I really appreciate this.</i>

473
00:29:13.583 --> 00:29:16.625
- [Phila] <i>Real quick. Pose for a photo.
- Okay.</i>

474
00:29:17.208 --> 00:29:21.000
[Phila] <i>Hold it... Hold it...</i>
[starts laughing]

475
00:29:21.083 --> 00:29:22.963
<i>- Dude. is this a video?</i>
- [Phila] <i>It's a video!</i>

476
00:29:23.041 --> 00:29:26.541
<i>- Come on. man!</i>
- [Phila laughs] <i>Oh. bro.</i>

477
00:29:26.625 --> 00:29:28.208
[phone jingles]

478
00:29:35.750 --> 00:29:38.000
[Grace in Sotho] Phila! Where is Phila?

479
00:29:38.083 --> 00:29:39.375
[music fades]

480
00:29:39.458 --> 00:29:41.666
[Grace] Phila! Phila!

481
00:29:43.166 --> 00:29:44.291
[in English] Phila.

482
00:29:45.625 --> 00:29:48.375
I need you by my side tomorrow
when the announcement is made.

483
00:29:48.458 --> 00:29:49.291
Done. Sure.

484
00:29:49.375 --> 00:29:53.833
We need to make it clear that my takeover
is a united family decision.

485
00:29:53.916 --> 00:29:55.676
[in Sotho] It's why
we have to live with him.

486
